### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

core

### Description

If we want to use cached data on resources, we have to use `startWith` in our observables, but that's not great, because we loose the functionality of `isLoading`, as that will be immediately true. 

Currently defaultValue would be a great place for that, but defaultValue doesn't accept dynamic values (callback fn that can return a different value everytime it's called), and this makes it painful to have resources that use cache data.

```ts
class UsersListStore {
	private readonly currentCachedItems = computed(() => {
		return this.usersGlobalStore.getEntitiesByFilters(this.currentFiltersPayload());
	});

	// WITHOUT REACTIVE DEFAULT VALUE, needs rxjs operators
	readonly usersRes = rxResource({
		params: () => this.currentFiltersPayload(),
		stream: ({ params: payload }) => {
			return this.usersApiService.getUsers(payload).pipe(
				tap(result => {
					this.usersGlobalStore.storeResultsAndFilters(result.items, payload);
				}),
				startWith({ items: this.currentCachedItems(), total: this.currentCachedItems().length }),
				filter(x => x.total > 0)
			);
		},
	});
}
```

### Proposed solution


```ts
class UsersListStore {
	private readonly currentCachedItems = computed(() => {
		return this.usersGlobalStore.getEntitiesByFilters(this.currentFiltersPayload());
	});

	// WITH REACTIVE DEFAULT VALUE, no need for rxjs operators
	readonly usersRes = rxResource({
		defaultValue: () => ({
			items: this.currentCachedItems(),
			total: this.currentCachedItems().length,
		}),
		params: () => this.currentFiltersPayload(),
		stream: ({ params: payload }) => {
			return this.usersApiService.getUsers(payload).pipe(
				tap(result => {
					this.usersGlobalStore.storeResultsAndFilters(result.items, payload);
				})
			);
		},
	});
}
```

### Alternatives considered

We can use a getter but that's not great ðŸ‘€

```ts
class UsersListStore {
	private readonly currentCachedItems = computed(() => {
		return this.usersGlobalStore.getEntitiesByFilters(this.currentFiltersPayload());
	});

        get resourceDefaultValue() {
           return {
			items: this.currentCachedItems(),
			total: this.currentCachedItems().length,
		};
        }

	// WITH REACTIVE DEFAULT VALUE, no need for rxjs operators
	readonly usersRes = rxResource({
		defaultValue: this.resourceDefaultValue,
		params: () => this.currentFiltersPayload(),
		stream: ({ params: payload }) => {
			return this.usersApiService.getUsers(payload).pipe(
				tap(result => {
					this.usersGlobalStore.storeResultsAndFilters(result.items, payload);
				})
			);
		},
	});
}
```

### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

core, animations

### Is this a regression?

Yes

### Description

New animation API looks great, but it does not provide all features that we were able to use in old animations api. 

For example:

You have two components rendered dynamically using `ngComponentOutlet` and you want to animate their entrance and their exit.

**ab.component.ts**
```ts
import {Component, ChangeDetectionStrategy} from '@angular/core';

/**
 * AB sample component
 */
@Component(
{
    selector: 'ab',
    templateUrl: 'ab.component.html',
    changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush
})
export class AbComponent
{
}
```

**ab.component.html**
```html
<div style="font-size: 32px; color: red; font-weight: bold;">AB</div>
```


**cd.component.ts**
```ts
import {Component, ChangeDetectionStrategy} from '@angular/core';

/**
 * CD sample component
 */
@Component(
{
    selector: 'cd',
    templateUrl: 'cd.component.html',
    changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush
})
export class CdComponent
{
}
```

**cd.component.html**
```html
<div style="font-size: 20px; color: blue; font-weight: bold;">CD</div>
```

**home.component.ts**
```ts
import {Component, ChangeDetectionStrategy, signal, Type, WritableSignal} from '@angular/core';
import {animate, group, query, style, transition, trigger} from '@angular/animations';
import {NgComponentOutlet} from '@angular/common';

import {AbComponent, CdComponent} from '../../../components';

/**
 * Home component
 */
@Component(
{
    selector: 'home-view',
    templateUrl: 'home.component.html',
    imports:
    [
        NgComponentOutlet,
    ],
    animations:
    [
        trigger('queryAnim',
        [
            transition('* => *',
            [
                group(
                [
                    query(':enter',
                    [
                        style(
                        {
                            position: 'absolute',
                            top: 0,
                            left: 0,
                            opacity: 0,
                        }),
                        animate('1000ms', style(
                        {
                            opacity: 1,
                        })),
                    ], {optional: true}),
                    query(':leave',
                    [
                        style(
                        {
                            position: 'absolute',
                            top: 0,
                            left: 0,
                        }),
                        animate('1000ms', style(
                        {
                            opacity: 0,
                        })),
                    ], {optional: true}),
                ]),
            ]),
        ]),
    ],
    changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush
})
export class HomeComponent
{
    protected type: WritableSignal<Type<unknown>|null> = signal(null);

    protected typeName: WritableSignal<string|null> = signal(null);

    protected next(): void
    {
        if(this.type() == null)
        {
            this.type.set(AbComponent);
            this.typeName.set(AbComponent.name);
        }
        else if(this.type() == AbComponent)
        {
            this.type.set(CdComponent);
            this.typeName.set(CdComponent.name);
        }
        else
        {
            this.type.set(null);
            this.typeName.set(null);
        }
    }
}
```

**home.component.html**
```html
<div>
    <div>
        <button type="button" (click)="next()">click</button>
        <div>{{typeName()}}</div>
    </div>

    <div style="position: relative;" [@queryAnim]="typeName()">
        <ng-container *ngComponentOutlet="type()"/>
    </div>
</div>
```

When you want to create one animation for all components rendered via `ViewContainerRef`, that are animated in one place, you can do it using `query(':enter')` and `query(':leave')` with old API and define it only once in code. You can easily reuse this animation.

But if you want to do this in new animation API, its not possible. I think `query(':enter')` can be done by using `@starting-style`, but there is no way to animate leaving component, so `query(':leave')` has no alternative in new API. Workaround for this would be define it on `AbComponent` and also on `CdComponent` but you have to have it already in two places and if number of these components is much higher, then you will have to repeat this code in every component which is not good for clean code. I hope at least you would be able to use `hostDirectives` with definition of host (i have not tried it yet) so you will only repeat usage of this directive but still it requires changes in every component.

This also applies for `RouterOutlet`, i know there are page transitions, but these are not supported for Firefox yet. But old animation API works perfectly even in Firefox.



